text: The William Street Bird, is a place in the city of Perth in Australia where people dance, drink, and play music. It started in 2010.https://web.archive.org/web/20190815124831/https://thewest.com.au/news/wa/community- radio-station-rtrfm-921s-radiothon-2019-is-set-to-kick-off-tomorrow- ng-b881292654zhttps://web.archive.org/web/20221128220345/https://tonedeaf.thebrag.com/tame- impala-members-form-new-band-for-fundraising- gig/https://web.archive.org/web/20220929074112/https://www.theurbanlist.com/perth/a-list/best- bars- northbridgehttps://web.archive.org/web/20210514103005/https://concreteplayground.com/perth/bars/the- bird There are some famous bands that started playing there, and later became famous. The names of some famous bands that started there include Flume, Stella Donnelly, Tame Impala, and Methyl Ethel. It is an important place in Perth for young people to find fans and grow their careers. Lots of people got practice by playing there. Sometimes not-famous people can also sing there. Sometimes artists show people their new music there. == References == Category:Perth, Western Australia
